D.q[3298] = "I\'m glad to see that young adventurers like you still go to the library from time to time. You know, before, there were lots of shops and workshops here. But when the Dragoturkeys arrived, all the shopkeepers started breeding! It\'s a lot more profitable! When the shops were sold, there was enough money to build all these paddocks... and our wonderful library.";
D.q[6501] = "You\'re looking for someone to help you catch a Brakmarian around the Tower of Bonta!? Aww, pick me man, please.";
D.q[3911] = "I didn\'t expect anything less from you. Fallaster, the King\'s brother, wishes to marry his daughter the princess Allisteria to a worthy man. Obviously, this is the King\'s responsibility and I\'m honoured I can help him in this task. We must find a suitor. Search a suitor of noble lineage and come back when you have found our gem.";
D.q[4387] = "The highest authorities got wind of your actions. The bandits were found, and you personally got hold of these documents. I know that you\'re honest. But not everyone is of the same opinion. I\'m going to have to take you off the case. What I can do is give you back your position in the militia. In the meanwhile, you\'re in charge of the supplies. Some cooked ham should do the job, but I don\'t want any of that fatty stuff. Our militiamen deserve the best... well, the second best, there\'s no need to take out a loan or anything. Then distribute it to militiamen Shere Hacanon, Finche Aticus et Kit Dingaround.";
D.q[644] = "The world of Dofus is rather unusual...\nit\'s an eventful universe and lately some nasty creatures have been invading the plains, fields and mountains.\nFor the moment, the villages are the only safe places.\nThe further away from a village you go, the more dangerous it will get. But that\'s the price you pay for glory. \n\nIn Amakna, the entire economy is controlled by the warriors and craftsmen, and trade between them is vital.\nIf you misbehave, you might be named a rogue (demon wings) and get chased off by the dispensers of justice (angel wings). \nMake the right choices and be careful... if you mess up you could go to jail.";
D.q[4938] = "You?! Here you are at last!";
D.q[1921] = "At the moment I need labourers - I\'ve more and more apprentices and less and less ingredients in stock. I still have enough raw materials left thanks to the numerous miners and lumberjacks who have been helping me, but I\'m short of rare materials. Would you mind bringing some to me? I\'ll pay you.";
D.q[3773] = "Have another go if you want. You need the practice! Don\'t worry about him, the magical winds of Incarnam breathe eternal life into this scarecrow.";
D.q[2133] = "If you bring me 5 Gobbly wool of each colour, I\'d make a small cape just for you!";
D.q[2659] = "Actually I\'ve a favour to ask of you. I\'d like you to go visit Amine at the Xelor Temple and give him this letter to warn him of the dangers that await us... As for me, I\'ll keep looking for a way to stop the inevitable...\n\nI\'ll add a couple precious minutes to your life\'s sandglass if you do this for me...";
D.q[3685] = "In your quest diary, click on the \'objective\' tab. The arrow on your compass will point the way to Shaa Kwira, if you\'re nice to her, she might even sing you a little song!";
D.q[2018] = "At last! Have you brought everything? That\'s great! The time has come to take our revenge! Right, I\'m going to put this together... *She looks at the wooden frame, is intrigued, then resumes putting the artefact together*...";
D.q[2286] = "You need to know one thing however - if you accidentally offend one of them, they\'ll certainly look for their revenge... Nothing too bad... like they might eat a limb off or something. Haha! Or crush your bones! So, listen to me, carefully...";
D.q[4923] = "If you don\'t bring me what I asked for, I\'ll never be able to make the doll.";
D.q[4326] = "A letter?";
D.q[248] = "What do you know about the art of the whip? Come back when you have a forked tail and horns!";
D.q[3299] = "If you don\'t know where the library is, don\'t hesitate to ask someone.";
D.q[2323] = "Our Cra friends have weird ideas sometimes. They take advantage of infectious aged-aunts that are present in those Arachnee legs to make poisoned arrows! Weird, but efficient... If you wanna make a little money, bring me 20 of those Arachnee legs. Somethin\' tell me I\'m goin\' to have to throw my sandwiches away... *sigh*";
D.q[1610] = "Our people are slowly but surely carving out a place for themselves in this World. Recently, the goddess revealed the sublime, ultimate art of the Sacriers to us. We are sharing this knowledge with any other Sacriers worthy of knowing these fighting techniques.";
D.q[6703] = "Captain Starky is waiting inside.";
D.q[3306] = "If you don\'t know where the library is, don\'t hesitate to ask the way.";
D.q[5924] = "If you found me, it is only because I wanted to be found. Explain why you came and I\'ll see if I\'m going to punish you or not for disturbing me.";
D.q[4633] = "If we want to make Elturt talk, we need to know more about him. I\'m entrusting you with this mission not for your skills, but because my other poodles are already on another mission. It would be in your interest to succeed this time because I find it difficult to tolerate repeated failures. No, the other militiamen\'s incompetence is not an excuse!\nStart by checking with an expert on animals, like that coward Oshimo, who looks after the Kennel.";
D.q[5912] = "If you don\'t like the new flowery decorations I\'m putting up, well you can just run off crying to your mummy.";
D.q[3799] = "Don\'t celebrate you SLUG! I handed you the fight \'cos we need foolish cannon fodder like you to battle the demon Rushu.";
D.q[418] = "Some warriors originally from Amakna decided to join the ranks of most powerful cities such as Bonta or Brakmar.\nIn order to spread their ideology, they sometimes attack the inhabitants of the region of Amakna in the hope they\'ll convince them to join their ranks. As long as you\'ll stay in neutral land, the garrison of Amakna will help you. However, once out of this zone, it will be at your own risks...";
D.q[2276] = "Haven\'t we met somewhere before? Let me think... Wasn\'t it near the plains of Cania, on a Lousy Pig hunt?";
D.q[2777] = "If you pass the test and you get enough information from Wally, go talk to Lanseuft who is guarding the way into the Damned Forest. Summon a special authorization from your Master to get through. One last piece of advice - if you know any other adventurers, team up with them before you venture into the forest... this way, you\'ve some chance of seeing me again!";
D.q[3322] = "Koalak Mountain was not very well mapped out. I\'d like some young, curious, and above all courageous adventurers to bring me back a precise description of this distant region... ";
D.q[1892] = "Hoho! Look at this... the apprentice of my dreams... I always wanted a soft young thing like you... the kind you can get to run errands at the other end of the land and who\'ll always come back smiling... ah, poverty\'s a great thing! Anyway, if you want a job, I need someone to make a survey of the area, to tell me where the most flowers grow. I\'m making a map of the most common species.";
D.q[581] = "But therrrrre is a missssssssing part *hic* wiiiithout it I can\'t do annnnnything *hic* I\'d be liiiike a big Gobballllll *hic* with neither hoooorns nor noooose *hic*";
D.q[3175] = "But... I\'ve a feeling I know you...\nYou\'re the one in charge of cleaning excrement in the Tofu House!\nPerfect timing! There\'s a lot for you to do right now! Hehe!";
D.q[3629] = "Well, well, you can use that sword, kid... Keep fighting like that and you won\'t stay poor for long.";
D.q[4612] = "What news have you brought me?";
D.q[2351] = "Well, you know, Dofus and all that stuff... You know, dragon eggs that give powers, you can\'t find a lot of that around, and with all those adventurers arriving, it\'s the egg rush! Well, I gotta go, have a good trip! And may the stones be soft under your feet!";
D.q[3606] = "Ahh, let\'s see what we have here. Ahh, good... this is good! Well, you can use these tools to work on your materials.";
D.q[2101] = "Go on, get out of here, I\'ll easily find other young people... there\'s cleverer people than you going around you know!";
D.q[4673] = "But!? Who are you? Why are you searching here?";
D.q[5719] = "I mentioned your case to several order masters and they\'re prepared to test your worth. Go to the Tower of Orders in Brakmar and discuss your path with them.\nTry not to hurry... you could even go have a drink at the Inn. Round here we don\'t like militiamen who rush their training. And remember, you\'re not obliged to decide on a precise path right away.";
D.q[108] = "What place are you looking for, exactly?";
D.q[5373] = "";
D.q[4403] = "I\'m joking. So, tell me, have you put on weight since we last met?";
D.q[5925] = "";
D.q[5926] = "";
D.q[2912] = "How come you\'re visiting me faithful Squire?\nShouldn\'t you be practicing with the militia?";
D.q[2075] = "Ah, I can imagine. This meeting was of great importance. To thank you, I\'m going to teach you the art of the Cras. What do you mean? I don\'t look like a warrior? It\'s not fashionable to look like a warrior anymore! A Gobball set, now that\'s class. Plus, it\'s a real lady magnet... ha ha...Sorry, I\'m wandering!";
D.q[6066] = "";
D.q[1974] = "Come on! I know zat I felt somezin\' like a shovel on my faze, but zat\'s not ze problem! I \'ave zome very important information, but the Enutrof zat surprized me now has my rebort in his bossession, and if he uzez it, I\'m finsht! You underztand?!";
D.q[127] = "In general, bows are made with twisted Flax Strings. I spend a lot of time making my bowstrings, they\'re particularly robust, but flexible at the same time. \nIf you\'re looking for Flax String for your bows, I can exchange some for a unit of Flax.";
D.q[6210] = "If I were you I\'d think long and hard about this. Many militiamen patrol these parts - all I\'ve to do is scream and they\'ll come running. \nIf you want some excitement, why don\'t you come and work for us? Some brave souls have a thing for women like you, believe it or not.";
D.q[6111] = "My name is Nudcan McLoad. I came to help someone who lost their pet, but it was an ambush. I\'ve been going round in circles in these caverns ever since.";
D.q[3670] = "Wooha, you\'re becoming too strong for Incarnam! You should go to Amakna... NOW.";
D.q[1886] = "Oh, you\'d do that for me?! Okay, let me explain. Tonight, I\'ve a date with lady Seria - it\'s been planned for a month. But Miss Fita just came back from her holidays and she asked me out tonight! I\'m supposed to leave Lady Seria and meet Miss Fita at exactly the same time. But, the two places are too far away from each other...";
D.q[205] = "Dopples are strange beings who mimic the behaviour of others in order to survive. No one really knows where they come from. One day they appeared in great numbers and tried to invade Amakna. We won that war and ever since we\'ve not really seen many around.";
D.q[2063] = "Hey, I sent my kid to pick you up. She\'s full of energy you know, and so strong... Just like her father, ain\'t that right chicken? I\'m representing the Cras at the Astrub Council. And I\'ll need your help.";
D.q[4960] = "I advise you to address me with a little more respect. Believe me, if I wanted to slap the life out of you, these little handcuffs wouldn\'t make the slightest difference.";
D.q[1968] = "Well, it wasn\'t the best fight I\'ve ever seen, but you did well, I suppose. I\'m the boss. What do you want?";
D.q[6120] = "Mmmh... I see, nothing too glorious then. In any case, you managed to complete the missions I gave you and for this you deserve a place as a Guardian of Knowledge. Your knowledge will guide your comrades.";
D.q[4977] = "If you run into Domen, tell him that I\'ll soon find a way to kill him once and for all.";
D.q[5459] = "What rank do you wish to have in the militia?";
D.q[2381] = "Hold your horses, you cannot become a blacksmith like me in a twinkle. You first have to decide what kinds of weapons you\'re going to forge. You can choose several of them, but it will take up a lot of your time.";
D.q[2864] = "Greetings #1, your evil aura is growing bigger and bigger every day. I\'m very proud of you!\nWhat can I do for you?";
D.q[2982] = "Alright! I don\'t want to boast but I\'m quite a talented auspice. Will I read your future in a Gobball\'s entrails? In a Bwak\'s intestines? Mmm, no. I believe it\'s more likely to be readable in beer froth for you. Order one to our nice Tek Abir, and put it on your bill, hehehe!";
D.q[701] = "Before you leave this temple, go see my brother Tarazed. He\'ll teach you how to restore your energy through meditation.\nIf you\'re not patient enough, you\'ll have to restore yourself thanks to the Bakers\' breads, or the Alchemists\' potions.\nDon\'t forget to save up some Kamas if you want to buy any of them.";
D.q[3642] = "Perfect! Go round town and ask the inhabitants if everything\'s fine. I\'m waiting for your report!";
D.q[6578] = "One minute, let me think.";
D.q[2874] = "Hello, we are bankers. You can open an account here and you\'ll have a safe place in which to keep your property. Please note that each time you access your bank account, it will cost you #1 Kamas.";
D.q[5590] = "Great, we\'ll wait until she\'s been reincarnated and then you can go question her. For now, go back and join the ranks of my Dark Apprentices.";
D.q[2362] = "Ok, since you want it so much... You\'ll have to kill a Gobball as fast as possible - you have two minutes. Prove me you can do it and you\'ll be a hunter.";
D.q[457] = "Hello there... I\'ve been trying to saddle these Dragoturkeys for several weeks now, but all my efforts are in vain. \nCan we make it the subject of a trade?";
D.q[1930] = "Welcome #1! You must be wondering how I know your name! Easy, everything that happens round town makes it here sooner or later! You can learn everything you need to know while sipping on a pint of the good stuff.";
D.q[2441] = "The butcher prepares the animals that hunters slaughter in the fields and forests, usually providing the best cuts of meat and sometimes cooking them too. You\'ll soon have many hungry and wealthy meat-eating mouths to feed, if you work hard. It\'s good for the little carnivores too, apparently.";
D.q[2660] = "Sorry, I don\'t have time to talk to you, the Divine Clock is losing time... It may sound impossible, but in fact, a gap in the temporal system can happen at any time! I\'m the guardian of time. I mustn\'t take my eyes off the clocks!\n\nFive minutes before each hour, I can take a quick break. Come back then if you want to talk to me.";
D.q[4422] = "And so what?";
D.q[3426] = "I\'ve got a lot of work. My wife takes care of the kids...";
D.q[251] = "With this, you can forge quality hammers, provided you know the relevant profession. I sell hammers if you need one, and if you don\'t have money, we can come to an agreement. I need some Gobball Horns, their shape and texture are perfect for...well, that\'s none of your business.";
D.q[1893] = "Thanks a lot! That gets me out of a tough spot, ha, ha!";
D.q[2269] = "Ohhh, thank you... thank you so much! Take my damaged scissors, you might need them!\n\nWhile you were gone, I, like, tried to sell a Sadidette wig to a lop, but, like, he was not buying! No way!\nI\'m telling you, it would be sooo cool if you could get that list of hair for me, seriously, that would be like so sweet of you!";
D.q[6780] = "If I make all the air around you disappear you\'ll be like a fish out of water. You\'ll open your mouth like this... *gob gob gasp gasp* and nothing will happen, you\'ll die!";
D.q[4966] = "Oh As\'Ruoy\'Dnim, gweat and powewful mastew. Obey As\'Ruoy\'Dnim. Conswuct the temple of As\'Ruoy\'Dnim.";
D.q[1907] = "Thank you very much. Could you do me another favour while you\'re at it? I\'ve heard that my delivery man wasn\'t sick at all but was chasing women instead of working. I\'d like you to spy on him a little bit to check whether that\'s true or not...";
D.q[7590] = "Hello, I suppose you want to get in to this magnificent house, don\'t you?";
D.q[6555] = "Good day, noble soldier. How can I help you?";
D.q[5938] = "";
D.q[7591] = "Your name is on the guest list, you can go in.";
D.q[2219] = "Wow... a Gloomy Calanthe Triplicata, hmm, I haven\'t seen such a specimen since my journey to Moon island...This public park is full of surprises!";
D.q[1811] = "If you want to challenge a Dopple, you must make a donation to the Eniripsa temple.\nIt will cost you a Flax Flower.";
D.q[5477] = "What rank do you wish to have in the militia?";
D.q[5939] = "";
D.q[7592] = "Well, what did you say your name was? Ah yes... Sorry, your name is not on the guest list. In other words, I\'m not allowed to let you enter.\n(Access to this location is reserved for premium members)";
D.q[5945] = "";
D.q[5861] = "";
D.q[1812] = "If you want to challenge a Dopple, you must make a donation to the Eniripsa temple.\nIt will cost you a Freyish Orchid.";
D.q[5479] = "What rank do you wish to have in the militia?";
D.q[1125] = "Consider this as a warning: keep your hands off me or I\'ll make sure you regret it.\n";
D.q[7037] = "I possess scrolls for all characteristics and all power levels. What power do you want your scroll to be?";
D.q[1813] = "If you want to challenge a Dopple, you must make a donation to the Eniripsa temple.\nThis time it will cost you an Edelweiss.";
D.q[2136] = "Ahh, not you again? Go and tell Mon\'Hawt\'Wit\' at the Eniripsas\' place before Joe loses his patience! Time is Kamas, and Joe loves Kamas, so you\'d better hurry the hell up!";
D.q[6000] = "";
D.q[5989] = "";
D.q[7553] = "Hello, I\'m delighted to see you.\nI need resourceful women like you to help me with my work. I\'ve an easy, well paid task to offer you, but you must be discreet and not ask questions.\nWhat do you say?";
D.q[3830] = "Well, well. The little sack of worms got out alive. I gotta say... you did alright. Okay, here\'s the reward. You deserve it.";
D.q[1656] = "The Imps are skilled in repairing, their new prism is already active, but it won\'t remain like this forever.";
D.q[2369] = "Welcome to the city of Astrub, eminent adventurer.\nIf you have any questions about the city and its surroundings, the mercenaries will do their best to answer.";
D.q[3801] = "You\'re lucky you\'re that weak. If you touched me, I\'d have sent you to the soul disco for wasting my time!\nI only challenge experienced adventurers. Go around Incarnam a few times and one day you might earn the right to die by my hand.";
D.q[1699] = "What luck! You\'ve just picked the genuine, unique Quaquack toy! It will follow you everywhere you go... but only if you want it to!\n";
D.q[5952] = "";
D.q[1789] = "If you want to challenge a Dopple, you must make a donation to the Osamodas temple.\nIt will cost you a Crackler\'s Stone.";
D.q[3333] = "I like trading with you. don\'t hesitate to come back.";
D.q[2964] = "To tell you the truth, the goddess Pandawa came and talked to me last night! She told me a flood will beat down on the World! And not a beer flood but a water flood... that\'s gonna be ugly! And, the goddess asked me to save two specimens of each of the creatures of this World! I\'ve already gathered quite a large part of them but I\'m still missing the Tofu eggs... Could you please bring me two of them back? You seem to be a bit scatterbrained, so write it down on your book! Check it to see what quests you\'re working on...";
D.q[5955] = "";
D.q[5994] = "";
D.q[5956] = "";
D.q[7556] = "I don\'t like to talk in public very much.";
D.q[3927] = "Strange things happening at the castle? Not really. We just had the visit of Allisteria. Usually, she never leaves her Gobballs alone. Oh, and the steward San Lavalss strictly forbids anyone to cook Wabbit at the castle.";
D.q[4329] = "Perfect. The last phase of our plan can begin.";
D.q[2924] = "Greetings. Your wisdom honours our god Jiva herself.\nHow can I help you?";
D.q[456] = "Lumberjacks are the main axe lovers. They often need a tool that can be used as a weapon in case they\'re attacked.\nTo forge an axe, you need to find wood of good quality to make a resistant shaft and appropriate metals for the blade.\nI can teach you this profession if you like.";
D.q[5097] = "";
D.q[385] = "I\'ll trade a Great Strength Scroll to anyone who can bring me 70 Prespic peaks, 75 Crab pincers and 40 Rib Chops. If I\'ve all those things then I\'ll be able to win the heart of Desde Mona, the woman I love. She wants a man who knows the feel of the stony bed of battle, who\'s been around the world a bit, you know.";
D.q[3003] = "You talked to Majistro? And he told you I wrote a book you\'d be interested in? What do you say? The Choice of Gods? Indeed, I wrote that book. Since Majistro sent you, I\'ll make you a cheap deal: let\'s say 40 Kamas! It\'s less than what you\'d pay at the library!";
D.q[2074] = "Ay! \'Urrywood, no less? Do you know where zis grows anyway? Well, I don\'t... Ze only sing I know it\'s zat merchant people bring it \'ere! Zey say iss VERY rare! What do you sink? Big deal... huh?";
D.q[1801] = "If you want to challenge a Dopple, you must make a donation to the Sacrier temple.\nIt will cost you a Scalding Poison.";
D.q[2027] = "AhAh... You\'re so wretched... I\'ll never get anything good out of you. Come back when you\'re worth your name...";
D.q[3356] = "You\'re smart, you\'re young, supple like I was once. Do a little twirl for me now... oh yeah, that\'s nice... you\'ll be quick!";
D.q[5961] = "";
D.q[2408] = "Oh I see, Kana Petch\'s bait. Take it and hurry, there are limits to his patience.";
D.q[2822] = "I\'m sorry I can\'t sell you alcohol... your internal organs would melt if you took a mouthful of this stuff!";
D.q[1971] = "I don\'t have time to find someone with experience, so you\'re gonna go down into the tunnels for me! Take this dagger, it might come in handy if something goes... wrong. I\'m sure you\'ve nothing to worry about! Gwahahaha!\n-Crack- Ouch! My pancreas!";
D.q[491] = "I have no missions for you right now. Get gone!";
D.q[3675] = "Further down this bridge, you\'ll find a balloon that will take you to Astrub or Pandala. Great adventures await for daring souls like yourself... alone or in company.";
D.q[2364] = "Yeah, not too bad! Well, excellent, I\'m going to make a hunter of you now, that\'s what you wanted, isn\'t it? You\'ll have to buy a hunter\'s tool in order to gather all the bits and pieces from your prey.";
D.q[5875] = "";
D.q[5480] = "What rank do you wish to have in the militia?";
D.q[2346] = "Go on, get lost!";
D.q[5057] = "Bloody idiot Wabbits. Even bigger idiots than you.";
D.q[5877] = "";
D.q[3847] = "The deal\'s simple buddy. You kill the Snoowolf and I hand over the money. If you try to mess me around, I\'ll drop you so hard... I\'ll be waiting at the exit.";
D.q[5878] = "";
D.q[2302] = "Oh yeah! Here comes my vegetarian pizznosh! Crap! I forgot my fidelity scroll again... I\'ll never get that free garlic bread!\nI hope their Lactuta sativa will be fresher than last time...";
D.q[7572] = "Which class temple would you like coordinates for?";
D.q[7560] = "Get lost, you\'ll draw attention to me.";
D.q[1861] = "Earmuffs are just what you need! Now, don\'t get me wrong, your ears are goooorgeous. But you need to protect them from the winter cold! Another winter like \'22 and where would we be? I\'m going to create something sooo special for you! First I need some rare raw materials...";
D.q[5490] = "What rank do you wish to have in the militia?";
D.q[3984] = "What a magnificent wegion! It looks like it\'s been painted by the gweatest awtist of all time!";
D.q[5879] = "";
D.q[2012] = "It drives me mad! These bloody Ecaflips won the bet again! I\'m going to find a way to beat that disgusting luck of theirs. If you agree to help me, I\'ll teach you powerful spells!";
D.q[2911] = "You have dishonoured your city by fighting outside the rules. Your bank account will be blocked until you regain your honour...";
D.q[6533] = "Damned rogues! They intercepted another delivery! Tell Amayiro to do his job and to protect honest merchants like me. I\'ll pay for the protection if he wants... actually, scratch that last bit.";
D.q[4801] = "Find the Sram who smells of fish and bring him back to me alive.";
D.q[5884] = "";
D.q[2417] = "Are you looking for information on a particular profession? Which category does it belong to?";
D.q[1803] = "If you want to challenge a Dopple, you must make a donation to the temple. It will cost you Vampire blood.";
D.q[4460] = "Is the tactician dead?";
D.q[3748] = "Making a healing potion is quite easy. Put on your gloves and go to the still, and use three flax flowers to one bucket of water - remember, the quantity is important. Normally, everything should go fine, but sometimes, the operation will fail. Don\'t get mad, get some more materials and keep trying.";
D.q[3971] = "Whaaat? Killed Wabbit? No inter, inter, no funny for big Bwork like me.";
D.q[5893] = "";
D.q[1802] = "If you want to challenge a Dopple, you must make a donation to the temple. It will cost you Vampiric Liquid.";
D.q[7573] = "Which class temple would you like coordinates for?";
D.q[2333] = "Whadda do YOU wanna? If you wanna to stay alive, getta outta here! Ana you didnitta see a ting.... OK!";
D.q[615] = "What happens now? My Master is dead... dead I tell ya! Sniff...";
D.q[6070] = "What have you come here for? Are you here on orders or were you just passing by?";
D.q[7596] = "Listen, here\'s what I suggest. \nEntertain me by fighting one of the creatures from my collection. If you win, I\'ll give you a present. \nYou can ask your friends to help - after all, many hands make light work, right?";
D.q[4045] = "What are you still doing here? You should really leave now.";
D.q[7482] = "";
D.q[7597] = "I see you\'re very motivated - that\'s a good thing. \nOne last point: once you\'ve defeated a monster, you\'ll never be able to fight it again. \nSo, tell me which monster you want to challenge. Try to put up a good fight, won\'t you.";
D.q[4346] = "What is a Brakmarian doing in these parts? Don\'t budge or I\'ll call the guard!";
D.q[5030] = "(The symbol on the safe is of a Dreggon. This is probably not what As\'Ruoy\'Dnim is looking for, even though there are undoubtedly worse things possible than this...)";
D.q[6752] = "I don\'t like people like you, you annoy me. And when I\'m annoyed, that\'s when I like breaking things that annoy me. Get it?";
D.q[7574] = "Which city would you like coordinates for?";
D.q[5895] = "";
D.q[7483] = "";
D.q[3026] = "You\'ll meet other adventurers next to the Kanojedo in Amakna. It\'s in the centre of the World. When over there, you\'ll be able to learn the traditions of Amakna. By the way, the Tavern of Amakna is very well-known for its parties... To travel at thought speed, I\'d recommend you use a Zaap. These magic arches come in very handy to travel around the World. When you see one, don\'t forget to touch it. This way, you\'ll memorize the location of the Zaap and you\'ll be able to come back to it later. Enjoy your trip! But before you go, I give you this book! You\'ll find it in your inventory. Read it when you can.";
D.q[2455] = "I thought he was bigger!";
D.q[4711] = "What\'s going to become of me? \nI\'m innocent, you hear... INN-OCCC-EEEENT!";
D.q[5408] = "What can I do for you?";
D.q[1133] = "Don\'t disturb the Great ZolTAN when he\'s up to his eyeballs in a transhynoptic trance. It could get on his nerves.";
D.q[7599] = "You\'ve already defeated all of the trophies that I had for you. Come back later, I need time to choose you a new opponent.";
D.q[7484] = "";
D.q[1928] = "In order to activate the magical power of the ring, you\'ll have to get it into a magical wave. It\'s very simple, you just have to fight a monster with a high magical potential like a treechnid. If the ring reacts positively, its magical power will be enabled. And remember you\'ll need help for sure.";
D.q[5898] = "";
D.q[421] = "You must practice a lot to become a good Blacksmith.\nYou also need to know how to work metals and different wood essences to forge basic weapons.\nThe most powerful weapons often need precious stones and rare metals with magic properties.";
D.q[5268] = "What\'s the word from the outpost?";
D.q[3352] = "To report a bug/problem you come across in-game, you can:\n\n- Click on the button in the top right-hand corner of the window next to the option menu\n- Write to technical support (http://support.Dofus.com/) in the Test Server section\n- Post on the forum under the Test Server section.\n\ndon\'t hesitate to contact the AnKama Team and submit any problem you come across here!";
D.q[7600] = "In fact, it\'s a bad idea. Any of my trophies would make mincemeat of you, and even if the idea of seeing your body scattered to the four winds amuses me, it\'ll make a mess and I do not want to clean up afterwards. \nCome see me when you\'re more experienced.";
D.q[4698] = "What do you want from me?";
D.q[7485] = "";
D.q[3360] = "You\'ve got it wrong sweetie pie.\nThe principle of such a Test Server is to test new functionalities in Dofus before everybody else to correct and fix persistent bugs, NOT to test your character... why I oughta...";
D.q[5046] = "What?! Bonta is occupying the Amaknean mines?! Over my dead body!";
D.q[7486] = "";
D.q[3810] = "A noisy noise annoys an oyster.";
D.q[7562] = "I know several of these people, they\'re drink sellers from the different villages on Pandala Island.\nShow me the crate. Would you mind if I opened it? No? Good.\nWhat... Look at all these bottles, do you have any idea what they might contain?\nI\'ll look after the crate for you while you take a bottle to Magus Ax. He works in the Alchemists\' Workshop, you\'ll have no trouble finding him. Give him the bottle and ask him to analyse the contents and then bring me the results.";
D.q[7487] = "";
D.q[5094] = "What? I was hoping I wouldn\'t see you so soon. What do you want?";
D.q[7577] = "Where else would you like coordinates for?";
D.q[3829] = "Hey, well done! You\'re alive! So, what do you wanna do? Get to the exit as quick as your little legs can carry you... or to the Inn to tell everyone what you\'ve done?";
D.q[4988] = "What? But... who are you?";
D.q[7563] = "You want me to analyse the contents of this flask because you can\'t do it yourself?\nWell, I suppose I can do it this time, but don\'t make a habit of it, OK?";
D.q[5622] = "Have pity. I\'ll confess everything, but please shut him up, please.";
D.q[6065] = "We acted quickly and suddenly, and that is exactly why the power of the Statues of Sumens is not in our possession right now.";
D.q[7488] = "";
D.q[1487] = "Patience is essential if you want to become a good fisherman. You\'ll have to buy me a fishing rod to train you with too. Good luck and all the best!";
D.q[7578] = "";
D.q[7551] = "Hello.\nIf you\'d like, I can give you some false documents that you can use to enrol yourself into the militia of your choosing.\nIn order to validate these documents, you need to be neutral, or match the city of your choice.\nWhat alignment would you like to have?";
D.q[7489] = "";
D.q[3849] = "Young peepil ishhh alwayshhh in a hurr... hic!... rry. They shhhould relakshhh. Enjoy HIC! life! A glasha Ginshher Ale, shhome friendshh, a beautiful waitreshh, nothing beatsh it!";
D.q[4492] = "Get there quick before the battle\'s over!";
D.q[7579] = "Continue your exploration, there\'s a lot more for you to discover.";
D.q[1788] = "If you want to challenge a Dopple, you must make a donation to the temple. It will cost you a Prespic tail.";
D.q[5545] = "If you want to experience the wonderful city of Astrub as well as the immensity of this World, you\'ll have to download the complete version of Dofus on the official website www.Dofus.com.";
D.q[1] = "I\'m one of #1\'s #5 perceptors.\nI can collect up to #2 pods of items.\nMy prospecting is #3, which allows me to collect loot from fights, but only after the fighters have been given their share.\nMy wisdom is #4, and helps my guild level up.";
D.q[7566] = "I can prepare some for you but I\'m short of Wilted Demonic Rose Petals. While you\'re fetching me one, I\'ll prepare the rest of the potion.";
D.q[1767] = "I\'ve trained some Dopples to fight like Cras. This way, they make good sparring partners no matter what your level is.\nMy goal is to train a Dopple until it\'s as powerful as Leffe Legodass himself, the famous Cra from Needle-Earth.";
D.q[3066] = "I can\'t wait! Could you go ask her out for me? Her name is Monabella. She lives in Allister\'s Castle and often wanders on the quays. Tell me when she\'s available.";
D.q[4932] = "We are the elite of the cite of Bonta and we don\'t waste time hanging around chatting when we\'re on a mission.";
D.q[5584] = "How are those 20 Scurvion Seeds coming along?";
D.q[727] = "If you wish to join the elite militia one day, first try to kill Crack Chafers.\nBrakmarians use Chafers when they attack. Therefore, it\'s vital to know their weaknesses. \nBring me 15 Chafer helmets to prove your value.";
D.q[7040] = "What characteristic should this scroll modify?";
D.q[2214] = "Oh! So, you\'re the back-up? Well, we\'ll have to make do... Okay, here\'s the situation: the Osamodas have lent us some Tofus to help us find gas leaks. They warn us in case of danger, ya see? We call them sniffallrats. \nI think they smelt somethin\' - but it ain\'t gas... Some of them came back in a pretty bad shape, and I don\'t think that Subosycold will do it any good. Ours left to find the Sniffallrats some time ago... I\'m afraid they have been captured by those bloody rats. Please, try to find them!";
D.q[3096] = "I can see you know where to find good beer. I\'d like to compare several of them.";
D.q[5909] = "";
D.q[1856] = "Welcome, step inside darling! OOOOHHH!!! Not just a pretty face. I\'ve friends who would kill for a body like that, get over here you vixen!!! I\'ve everything you need... let me be your tailor. Pleeeease. Mememememe! Ohhh thank you. But look at me, so rude... my name is Alit Elfminate, I put the TAIL back in TAILOR. Hee hee!";
D.q[4476] = "Who are you? What do you want? Stay away from me!";
D.q[2275] = "Get to know some Eniripsas. They\'re good doctors. Oh yeahhh, I forgot, there\'s this young Feca master, living to the east of Amakna... what\'s his name again? Can\'t remember...But he\'s a famous Gobball breeder, he even won a few awards at the Trool fun fair. He has lots of Small Scrolls of Vitality. Go and find him, he will surely give you some information on the matter!";
D.q[4882] = "Did my friends agree to help me?";
D.q[5192] = "You want help Ronan? So you attack convoy!";
D.q[409] = "I need to make a good custard tart with Tofu eggs to celebrate my cousin\'s return. But I need a Tofu egg. If you bring me one, I\'ll give you one of my Leather Cutters in exchange.";
D.q[4274] = "Who? Ah, it\'s not the last winner of the Gobball Slobber gathering contest, is it? No? Well I don\'t know then.";
D.q[2089] = "It\'s the very first time the Enutrofs have ever needed this remedy... Something must be going wrong underground. Would you mind investigating for me? Come back with a detailed report of anything out of the ordinary. Take this hammer, too. Hammers are good, know what I mean?!\nJust follow your compass.";
D.q[2341] = "I wonder if the Eniripsas will to find those Arachnee legs suspicious... I don\'t want to leave my supply behind... *sigh*";
D.q[6297] = "Here you are again, finally. I was wondering what you were up to. I hope for your sake you weren\'t plotting against me, or you\'ll pay a hefty price. A very hefty price.";
D.q[4271] = "Xephires? No, I don\'t know anything about it.";
D.q[2312] = "Hum... Hum... Are you sure you\'re eating enough? I\'m giving you this job out of pity, you pathetic little coat hanger... haha...";
D.q[4465] = "He\'s on the way to Astrub.";
D.q[2335] = "If you want a nice, filling beer... you\'re in the right place. Everybody knows that Astrub beer is not the lightest. Hahaha... So whaddya say!";
D.q[2064] = "Hey fella! You came to listen to the flowers grow? Something else? I knew it! You should give yourself a break from time to time to listen to nature, you\'re far too stressed out! Nature speaks in slow motion, but it\'s well worth sitting back and taking it in sometimes!";
D.q[6711] = "Thanks to you I earned a cartload of Kamas. You can tell your boss that I\'m his man. I\'ll be staying in Astrub for a few days on business, so he can contact me when he likes.";
D.q[5015] = "As far as I can see, he\'s not budging... take this to him from me.";
D.q[3011] = "Go see Zeurg, in the Osamodas Temple. He has strange customs... but he has Wisdom scrolls, which is even stranger!";
D.q[5386] = "Can\'t you see I\'m busy? I have more important things to be doing than chatting with tourists.";
D.q[5260] = "Have the territories been conquered?";
D.q[5185] = "See intruder. See intruder.";
D.q[6278] = "Once it\'s not mine you\'re on about, I\'ve got no problem with it.";
D.q[2125] = "Deliver this cake to grandma, be quick, and be careful because there are rats lurking around her house. They must not eat the cake.";
D.q[7559] = "What are you still doing here? You should have left already!";
D.q[7555] = "Perfect, I see that we are on the same wavelength.\nI don\'t want our conversation to leak out, so join me in my house. It lies south of the statue of the god Iop, near the Handymen\'s Market.\nI\'d prefer it if you avoided going through the main gate. Use the back door instead, it\'s more discreet and hidden by a pile of crates.\nI\'ll tell you more when you join me there.";
D.q[7554] = "That\'s a shame, I\'m sure we could do great things together. Well...\nI\'m not going to force you, but if you change your mind, you know where to find me.";
D.q[7048] = "Amazing, I can feel the power emanating from this object just by touching it. I\'ve never seen anything like it. This weapon is made in the image of Jiva: beautiful, light, fast and deadly.\nYou have served our great city well, and I know how to reward loyal subjects. Take this purse of Kamas and this Great Scroll of Vitality, they should be of some use.";
D.q[1383] = "If you\'re looking for the Bontarian warrior, he ran away northwards. You should be able to track him easily. Try to talk to the sentinels on your way, they might have seen him.";
D.q[2148] = "I see you have no weapon. Here, please take this purse, it\'s full of Kamas that Kwartzwatch kindly gave me. There should be more than enough for you to buy one. I think Kwartzwatch might have played a trick on me, though - the coins might disappear soon if no one takes them!";
D.q[7033] = "It will be difficult, the journey is very long and the sea is perilous. There are very strong currents, tidal waves, waves taller than the Tower of Gisgoul, not to mention the freezing temperature, the fog that creeps under your clothes and freezes your bowels, and the rations that such a crossing demands. On top of that, this island is the home of the Abominable Sept of the Seas, a hairy, voracious creature, with a ferocious appetite...\nI see you already have your ticket, couldn\'t you have said something earlier? I\'m really tired of hicks like you.";
D.q[2026] = "Bam... Tzzzz, stop stroking me. I don\'t need tenderness, I\'m not a pussy cat. Come back to see me when you\'re able to take on a Tofu... Hahaha.";
D.q[3284] = "The Kralove swallowed me but choked on my sponge items. It spit me out 2 months later, and I was still alive! I had eaten some of the pre-digested fish that were in its stomach to survive.\nYou may not believe me, but this is just excellent! Besides, it gave me some great recipe ideas based on pre-digested fish fermented in Oilbow Grease. Once I\'ve found clients, I\'ll be able to open a new franchise.\nBut let\'s stick to the point...";
D.q[5034] = "(The symbol on the safe is of a Demon. As\'Ruoy\'Dnim should like this one.)";
D.q[6338] = "The Whitish Fang soul isn\'t going to just appear in your pocket if you keep hanging around the militia, is it?";
D.q[6725] = ".........\n.................\n........................";
D.q[2192] = "That\'s a nice piece you\'ve got here! Well, it won\'t take long... Come back to see me in a minute...";
D.q[2244] = "Sorry... I\'m too busy to talk at the moment... I\'m training my Tofus to help the Enutrofs in their underground work.";
D.q[2122] = "Shovel... useless... ground... too hard... no digging... I need planks! Two chestnut tree planks...! \nFood! Survive? Yes... need bread... three loaves... Amakna Bread!";
D.q[5920] = "";
D.q[3285] = "Then, I discovered a strange sand castle on this rocky inlet and I ventured inside it like a courageous man looking for redemption or maybe digestion, I can\'t remember very well.\nI\'ve assailed the most disgusting sea creatures, even they wouldn\'t be scared of you.\nThat\'s when I got my sponge items back. For this, I had to cut up a monstrous sea sponge, the notorious Sponge Mob.";
D.q[6265] = "I\'m waiting to see the colour of your Kamas before taking a decision.";
D.q[2203] = "Well... you know, I\'m not ze person for the administration... neither the Tofus, by ze way... but some person must have to do it! SO! Why don\'t YOU do zis? Of course not! Joking! \'Ave a nice day anyway!";
D.q[1900] = "How can I take his mind off those two stupid little girls... I do have an idea but if he finds out it was me he\'ll go crazy. This is sooo random. *sigh*";
D.q[5546] = "What do you want, you pile of Trool dirt? I\'m an important Bontarian merchant, I don\'t have time to chat to your type.";
D.q[4284] = "As you like, but don\'t say I didn\'t warn you.";
D.q[5923] = "";
D.q[2283] = "A silly story... We were with some Sram mercenaries and a Moowolf trap closed down on us at the wrong time. I lost half my ear, but I\'m alright. But my brother Kouy... he wasn\'t so lucky.";
D.q[2324] = "What? Oh yes, grossewer rats...*sigh*...they\'re killin\' my business. There\'s a swarm of \'em down in the tunnels, frightenin\' the life out of me, but maybe a brave thing like yourself... well, brave I dunno, but maybe ye could get rid of a few? How bout ye kill 14 or so and I\'ll give ye a few Kamas... fella like you can kill three at the same time. That might frighten the others off... my business will be saved! ";
D.q[2147] = "Hehe! You have to be smart to win a bet against a Xelor. Some say they can see into the future... Right, now, though, she\'s dating this guy, she\'s in love... I knew it was the right time to bet... ha! They say love is blind, right!";
D.q[5928] = "";
D.q[6804] = "Then confiscate them, so they will be safe if something happens.";
D.q[2213] = "I... I can\'t find my house anymore... all I remember is that mummy often takes me to the village park... my house is near the park...";
D.q[3281] = "Hi! I\'m Fatchark, the famous captain! I\'m sure you\'ve already heard about me. Before being a captain with no boat, I used to be a cook. Yes! A cook! I used to prepare fish like no one, using alive fish! Right sir, alive! Then I\'d smash them and add some salt and magic herbs - that were also alive - to it! And my fish enabled those who ate it to breathe under water when they swam backwards. How come you don\'t believe me?! But I swear! Everything I\'ve said is true!";
D.q[6337] = "Before running off like a fool, bring me the soul of a Whitish Fang. I\'ll explain why later just in case you don\'t understand.";
D.q[5934] = "";
D.q[1466] = "Iik ik ink ibindinid skiril. Iik wild likik ti bik wit mik mimmik bik iik tiknik tkik shik his binik ciptirid... ";
D.q[5608] = "That wasn\'t everything, but I\'m absolutely knackered now, so I\'m going to have a little nap - wake me up if you need to.";
D.q[2268] = "What the hell? What did you do with that feather? You threw it away? Another one will cost you 5 Kamas...";
D.q[5975] = "Here you are at last! Where did you get to? Do you think you can just take off whenever it suits you?";
D.q[2238] = "What are you waiting for? Go and see Oli Venders like I told you! He\'ll probably be able to give you some Hurrywood.";
D.q[5976] = "";
D.q[4805] = "While I\'m here, Judge Satirev Onivin wants to see you before the trial. I suggest you don\'t make him wait too long.";
D.q[6097] = "";
D.q[4481] = "According to the letter from Xephires, the convoy will pass along the path at the edge of the Treechnid forest on its way to the Imp village. Intercept it before it arrives at its destination.";
D.q[2349] = "There is a limit on the number of objects you can sell at once.\nYou have to wait until some are sold before putting others on sale.\nAfter a while, if some items haven\'t been sold, they\'re taken out of the marketplace and put back directly in your safe at the bank.";
D.q[2389] = "Here come the reinforcements! So, it seems you came out of it unscathed... along with the Pyrite Brothers... but the poor fellows are in a sorry state! Bah!... Some Pandala fresh air will put them on their feet again! You should go see Surivitna. He\'s the Shaman of Pandala... You look quite peaky yourself...";
D.q[1584] = "Ikfik yik wik ti isik tik miricilis piwik, yik wilik nid ink gidik risinik inik ink icirnik.";
D.q[4469] = "Sorry, I\'m not taking any orders for the moment.";
D.q[4785] = "I was just curious, there\'s no harm in that.";
D.q[2914] = "The Tower is lit up by each of your visits. What do you need?";
D.q[6593] = "And how can you help me? How could you conjure a curse that is used by the gods themselves? Even my book of spells has nothing to match their skill. Every day is worse than the one before, I don\'t know how much longer I can last. I tried blocking my nose, but then I only have one hand left to hold my magic book and cast my spells. Believe me, it\'s not easy... and as for the cramps I\'ve been getting...\nBut you, you can leave this place and ask the wise men some questions. I heard that the councillors of your people have vast libraries. Maybe the solution lies in one of those books.";
D.q[2303] = "I think daddy\'s back from his meeting, he went back over to the lake.\nThanks again for the Arachnee.";
D.q[6764] = "Gimme a B\nGimme an O \nGimme an N\nGimme a T\nGimme an A";
D.q[2375] = "I\'m a wood sculptor, especially expert in wands, staffs and mostly bows, that I really like. \nBeing a carver is pretty hard, the raw material is quite rare, and you need to find an experienced lumberjack to stock up on the right stuff.";
D.q[7031] = "I expected no less from you. Now listen to me carefully.\nThe Dawn Shard cannot be forged just anywhere. You\'ll have to go to the Isle O\'Antitch with people you trust. Once there, find a Frozen Crystal to make a Frost Potion. Then, look for a cave cold enough to use the Frost Potion on the Wyrmwell to freeze the water, shatter it, and retrieve the Remembrance Fragments. When this is done, head to the heart of the island with your companions to forge the weapon destined for the great Jiva.\nI\'m let Kosuke Ichazum know he should join you there.";
D.q[410] = "You can deposit Kamas and items in your bank account.\nYou can only have one bank account. \nEvery time you access your bank account, even if you\'re just having a look inside, you must pay a fee.\nThis fee depends on the number of items stored in your bank account.";
D.q[3534] = "Be careful! Dark Miners are close, I can feel it, they\'re on their way, we\'re surrounded! Get rid of them and jump in the waggon! QUICK!";
D.q[3456] = "My great grandfather was the one who started building the railway between the different mines of the region.\nI spent a lot of time looking after them and I noticed that there was an incredible number of unexplored tunnels...\nMy ancestors always said there was a village hidden beneath one of these mountains above us that could only be accessed through one of the old mines. Unfortunately, we still have not found it. My faith in my grandfather is still strong... I know I\'ll pierce this mystery even if I\'ve to dig through the damned rock!";
D.q[2404] = "Being a Shoemaker is a hard job, it requires time and money. You need to know the right people to get the appropriate leather and raw materials you need to make good belts or boots. But it\'s worth it, believe me!";
D.q[2290] = "A hairy creature of the size of a Miliboowolf that attacks the Gobballs at night? Hm, it sounds like the work of the Bearman... Perhaps you\'ve heard of this fellow... who can control bears. They say that all his power comes from an old Osamodas manuscript. If you steal it from him, you\'ll stop this terrible Gobball slaughter, but remember, you cannot succeed alone. Unless you challenge him with a group of adventurers, he will not use his scroll... first things first though... you\'ll need to find his lair first. It shouldn\'t be difficult - this kind of creature always leaves trace behind...";
D.q[4270] = "Who? Oh, it\'s not the most recent winner of the Gobball Saliva Collecting Contest, is it? No? Meh, I dunno \'em then.";
D.q[2370] = "I\'m all ears, which market are you looking for?";
D.q[1894] = "As for me, I\'ve hardly polished up my buttons and already I\'ve found a few interesting clues: pebbles...*he thinks* We should try to find out where they come from.";
D.q[4512] = "Impressive! With weapons and equipment of this standard our troops won\'t just equal the Brakmarians, they will surpass them! You have done very well. Take a few potions to get you back in shape.";
D.q[2978] = "If I catch anyone with one of these fake eggs, I can assure you that the shh...ugar will hit the fan!";
D.q[5665] = "I\'m just putting the finishing touches on a new plan. I don\'t want to be disturbed.";
D.q[4402] = "Password?";
D.q[7614] = "You, who dares set foot in what was once a thriving village, now destroyed by the madness of men, you\'re too late.";
D.q[4452] = "I\'m off right now! I\'ll try not to get involved in that kind of altercation in future...";
D.q[1879] = "This is mine house. Do you want to meet mine sister? don\'t make any silly in mine house, I\'ll take knife and cut you...";
D.q[2409] = "Whaat? Where are the scissors I gave you? They might be damaged, my little friend, but they\'re like.... they\'re special to me. You know a new pair\'ll cost you, like, 50 Kamas?";
D.q[1871] = "The Rogues, you say? Hmmm, why would they want to make my house vanish?";
D.q[2021] = "Humm...The Sacriers Goddess has confided in me that you\'re worthy to join our ranks... but I\'ll have to see for myself of course...There are 3 important things in a Sacrier\'s life. The first is to be hit first in a fight. The second is to take a lot of beatings. The last one, well, I forgot...";
D.q[1873] = "Think about it and get the culprit here. Don\'t come back without him! Talk to the alchemist if you need something analysed. Don\'t hesitate to threaten or bribe the people you question. I WANT to know where my HOUSE is!";
D.q[2264] = "Wow, I\'m so impressed!!! But it makes me sad that you\'re not interested in my job, you know, cos, it\'s like, yesterday, I was like, \'yeah, I wish I had an assistant like that\', you know, and well...";
D.q[4501] = "I told you I didn\'t want to get mixed up in all this.";
D.q[1912] = "I\'ve got 3 dates at the same time. How do you think I\'m feeling? I... hum... hu... I\'m sick...Oh, blow it! I\'ll survive. I suppose the baker sent you... Tell him I resign! I\'m only delivering dangerous goods from now on! I need some excitement in my life!";
D.q[3044] = "Allister\'s Castle finally opened its gates. The King moped in his apartments during all the works. Now, strolling players, Trool leaders and troubadours will soon be flooding in. You should go visit the new facilities of the castle and its harbour.";
D.q[2736] = "In Pandala, we always find something to ferment. And we always find a way to make first class hooch out of it! But be careful, don\'t drink too much of the hard stuff - it could make you attack perceptors and... let them live.";
D.q[1867] = "Do you want to help me? Well, you might be able. First, go and find as many clues as possible, you\'ll be rewarded for everything and anything you bring back to me. I\'ll indicate the location of my former house on your map.";
D.q[358] = "In a big pot, fry 80 Acorns, 80 Tongues of Evil Dandelion, 80 Rose Petals and then chuck in about twenty doses of Mush Mush Sporm. You\'ll get a soup so creamy you won\'t believe it! \nI\'m licking my lips just thinking about it...";
D.q[2200] = "I knew you\'d like it. So let\'s have a peek into the future... What? You think it\'s cheating?... Let\'s get one thing straight, my young apprentice, a Xelor never cheats! They... anticipate... it\'s just smarts! So, as I was saying, I\'m going to need some materials: two crystal phials of pale Anthir from Dragonsly, the alchemist, Epyss grain, you\'ll get that from one of the workers at the food warehouse and wood from Oli Venders. Simple wood, untreated! The wood determines how far you go into the future, and I don\'t need to see far. Take these directions to Dragonsly\'s house... follow your compass.";
D.q[6510] = "ahahahahahhaahahah\nHAHAHAHAHHARHARHARHHAA!\nYou\'re poor, you don\'t have a coin in your pocket and you think you can survive in Brakmar?\nHahahhahaaahahaaahaha\nHARHARHAHARHARHAAHA!";
D.q[4486] = "I didn\'t know that the militia building in Brakmar was next to the Port of Madrestam. What are you doing here?";
D.q[1181] = "You want to become a butcher? It\'s simple you know. The basic technique of Monster Cutting uses the same fundamental movements as the ancestral style. Once you get the knack, it\'s just a matter of practice. \nShall we go on?";
D.q[6824] = "I don\'t spend my entire life in this cellar, even if I do enjoy coming here. To be honest, it\'s the outdoors that I love most. I wish I could fly with my own wings, over the Cania Plains and the Asse Sea. But we have to face facts, it will never happen. However, what is possible, would be to convert the public paddocks into rings for Tofu fights.\nAfter all that, no, I do not know a Sram who stinks. You should tale to customers who are here more often, like those three weirdoes over there, near the arena.";
D.q[1869] = "Birds would have eaten my entire house? When I think about it, it might not be that crazy... One of them did look at me cross-ways the other day... a kind of an evil eye, you know.";
D.q[6720] = "I need help from an Osamodas who knows the spell Natural Defence and an alchemist who can make Phoenix Blood to enchant the stone.";
D.q[3705] = "As soon as I turn 15, I\'m getting out of this village. I\'m going to be an adventurer and I\'m going to visit the outskirts of that city down there. I can just about make it through the mist. It\'ll be dangerous, but if I practice really hard hunting Gobblies, soon I\'ll be able to kill a Gobball. Kill one with my bare hands, too.";
D.q[3578] = "Some doubt my courage... my courage! I\'ve never run from an enemy. I mean, I haven\'t had too many enemies, but still. You don\'t get where I\'m without talent. That\'s what my captain used to say... he said I\'m the best.";
D.q[4540] = "I see who\'s coming. Advance! For Bonta!";
D.q[3708] = "Over there... oh man, everything\'s new... wild. They say if you got some brains and a heart of stone, you can make a fortune... I don\'t know if I\'ve either. Someday, huh?";
D.q[3601] = "Sure, but let\'s not get carried away. Before you can actually concoct powerful potions, you must collect all the ingredients. Shall I show you how to do it?";
D.q[3824] = "Well, don\'t waste your energy little midget, my answers are always the same. My job is to explain what happens in these caves. Think of me as the craziest, meanest tour guide you\'ve ever seen. Well, kid, there\'s monsters in this cave will drop you so hard, you\'ll be scooping your guts up with a broken arm. If you stay alive long enough, you\'ll get to their chief. 1,000 pounds of break your bones, mean as hell meat. You stupid enough to go you sack of dead worms? Well, get some buddies together, stand on the SLABS and take a look.";
D.q[1881] = "Here\'s my address... I live in the South of the city. You can\'t miss my house... its surrounded with plants!\nThere\'s a well a little west of the house too, if you don\'t know where to look for water...";
D.q[3809] = "I\'m a father pheasant plucker, I pluck father pheasants. I\'m the best father pheasant plucker, that ever plucked a father pheasant!";
D.q[3792] = "To add a friend to your list, just click on the character and click \'add to my friends\', and hey presto, they\'re in your book! Now show me you understood alright... add a character to your friend list.";
D.q[3771] = "Before you continue, young one, I advise you to knock this scarecrow up a bit. Round I mean... knock it round. Cast a few spells, attack him with all you have. It won\'t always be this easy, so learn what you can!";
D.q[4507] = "Well? What do I care if Bonta\'s in difficulty? I just want you to leave me alone.";
D.q[1744] = "Ecaflips are very strong characters, but they\'re always looking for things to help them get stronger";
D.q[2181] = "Oh, you\'re here for Locette, I\'ve been thinking of her. I thought of an ancestral remedy that could work in her case: a potion so hot and so stinky that her senses will be revived. Fight fire with fire, that\'s my motto. I need a large quantity of Gobball\'s saliva, a bit of evil rose saliva, and some Mush Mush Thorns. Bring me all these elements, please!";
D.q[3542] = "Xelor, time master, creator of the Amaknean Calendar. Xelor\'s path makes for a difficult journey, but a fulfilling one. I\'ll help you improve your skills... They\'re still strange to you, young one.";
D.q[6538] = "Amayiro asked me to help you, but now that more and more convoys are being attacked, I can\'t leave my men alone. Do you have any friends who could help you out? Otherwise you\'re on your own.";
D.q[3666] = "Finally! A new hammer to fix this damned Zaap!";
D.q[4338] = "I accept your terms. Don\'t stay here, they might sneak up on us!";
D.q[4342] = "Hello. What\'s brought you here, then?";
D.q[6325] = "Huh, what? But... ahhh!!!";
D.q[1943] = "Essence of Dizbi, yes, of course! Are you a new apprentice? Whose? Nepra\'s?... ahh... Nepra... hmmm... lovely, isn\'t she? I remember when I was her student myself, I could have spent hours... *sigh*";
D.q[6440] = "In spite of all the information you brought to the table, the council is still refusing to send troops to the Rocky Plains, saying that Bonta can\'t afford to have so many troops out on duty in the case of an attack from Brakmar. It just doesn\'t make any sense - our spies have reported nothing out of the ordinary in Brakmar. I really don\'t want to send you rushing into the lion\'s jaws, so I\'m going to assign you to another mission.";
D.q[3607] = "How does it work? Well it\'s easy. Choose the right bench for the job. When you have enough materials to craft something, the monitor will indicate so. Put all the materials on the workbench, and simply give the level a good hard yank to combine all the elements together. Remember that to enter the workshop, you must first have your tool out.";
D.q[3789] = "What\'s that story about a blinding light at the end of the tunnel?";
D.q[3681] = "Alright soldier, alright. Get into town and see if the people are doing okay. And hurry up maggot.";
D.q[3729] = "Laura\'s a bit too fervent for my liking, but she\'s a nice girl. Sit down, young adventurer, and I\'ll tell you an old story. Come on, sit here.";
D.q[6176] = "How do you expect me to react when an idiot sends me an incompetent fool? Brakmar doesn\'t need you, not for the moment at least.";
D.q[2000] = "What do you mean? Ok! I\'m preparing everything at once!... It won\'t take long at all... Take it and go away. *grmbl...*";
D.q[4381] = "A Xelor tried to buy the jewel and you refused? I knew I could trust you. Here\'s 1,000 Kamas to reward your integrity. Tell me when the convoy can leave. You\'ll be joining the escort.";
D.q[2348] = "Do you really believe that talking is enough for practising this profession? Well, this just means that you didn\'t get the spirit of it. If you really want to become an alchemist, go and see the chief instructor in Amakna, I\'ll show you where it\'s on your map if you like.";
D.q[3697] = "There\'s always a craftsman on the look-out for resources. They\'re a harvester\'s best source of Kamas.";
D.q[5647] = "Good, I can see You\'re motivated.\nWe\'re going to get our hands on some statues which symbolise the good and evil in humanity. When our task is over, the world will sink into despair, making conquest inevitable. \nDivad Dleifrepok has managed to find out where the statues are located, and you\'ll go there to take out the guards. You can take some companions with you if you like, that way you won\'t get bored. \nThe statuettes are hidden in an old abandoned mine near the Enutrof temple. Setag blocked up the entrance, but there should be a way to get in nearby. Have a good look around.";
D.q[3760] = "With your strength, you might take a scarecrow down in one go!!! Try not to burst them open altogether... I\'m the one who has to fill them up again afterwards!";
D.q[911] = "In the name of the holy Devil, there\'s an angel in Brakmar! Catch it!";
D.q[7602] = "On your way, woodlouse.";
D.q[3649] = "I was eating a big bowl of hot soap... no, what am I saying I was eating a big bowl of soup... that was funny, because just before, ah yes I remember, just before, I had shaved my...";
D.q[6468] = "You won\'t get off so easy this time!";
D.q[3286] = "So now I\'m sure you\'re wondering how I could make the Giant Kralove from Moon Island choke on my sponge items if I only got them after cutting up Sponge Mob?!\nWell, buddy, I see you\'re following what I\'m saying. It\'s easy! A long time ago, before I created Zaaps, I had created a time-travelling machine. \nThat\'s right, I built it when I beached on the famous Otomai Island.";
D.q[7603] = "It\'s awful, really awful...";
D.q[3663] = "Don\'t worry about that, you won\'t need many. You\'ll have found some on the creatures you\'ve defeated. The further the Zaap takes you, the more Kamas you\'ll need. Do you want to know the story of these magic portals?";
D.q[4608] = "Come back and see me when you have some news.";
D.q[5658] = "Greetings. I hope Terra Bitya is not mistreating you too much. Hahaha!";
D.q[5829] = "Greetings. Did you manage to conceive a Grande Fée d\'Artifice Hille?";
D.q[3695] = "A good harvester always keeps a close eye on his inventory. He should always keep some empty slots to store what he collects.";
D.q[3844] = "You brringin\' me back da ingrredient to make-a da painting. You\'re-a so-nice! You\'re-a an arrtist!";
D.q[5834] = "";
D.q[3717] = "When you go out into the big, bad world, you\'ll have to buy food if you want to heal your wounds. Nymphs won\'t help you then, they only aid the weak.";
D.q[5627] = "Incarnam is the best place to get some experience under your belt. I really don\'t know why most souls end up leaving that paradise on earth...";
D.q[4767] = "The last one\'s on the way. Prepare yourself.";
D.q[6055] = "";
D.q[7606] = "There you go, I\'ve shown you which monster took part in the break-in.\nDon\'t forget to bring the box of presents back to me as soon as you\'ve recovered it.\nYou can take as long as you like to get it back, but if despite your best efforts you aren\'t able to recover it, come back and see me in two hours.";
D.q[7607] = "I know you! You\'re one of the people I asked to recover the stolen boxes.\nHow are you getting on?";
D.q[4670] = "Hey, what has you over this way, did your canary die or something? I bet my last candle you want to get to the other side! I was like you once, a bit crazy but sharp at the same time, and often completely out of my tree... But bit by bit I got some bottle. Drank a few bottles too... But I always had a good reason... you know, to kill the bacteria in my throat... I had to drown them somehow and I thought the poor cretins deserved better than water for their last tipple. Well, are you gonna keep me here all day with your stupid tales?";
D.q[3688] = "What the...? You\'re tellin me you can\'t find a friend round here.... what\'s your major malfunction, soldier? Square yourself up... you keep me waiting and you\'ll be in a world of pain.";
D.q[2067] = "Indeed, Hurrywood is very rare but I could have done it with any other wood... Anyway, my partner is ready to take care of that. Right now, I\'m too exhausted, I\'ve been listening to Nature for more than an hour now... *yawns*";
D.q[4133] = "Incredible! You found everything I need to fix our ship. I\'m surprised that Flib\'s Cursed Chest gave you its little box... He may not have been that mad at me in the end.\nI can finally get started on my work while enjoying this delicious Kokoko juice. Let\'s make an extra effort and we\'ll then be able to leave this island.";
D.q[4940] = "Tell me what happened.";
D.q[7608] = "What, it\'s difficult, or you can\'t be bothered?\nWell, let\'s see. Which monster still has a stolen box...";
D.q[6178] = "Snori Nairb sent you? I\'m guessing you\'re here to join our beautiful city\'s Militia then, am I right?";
D.q[7142] = "Hello young adventurer. I don\'t know if you\'ve been told, but our temple has had a makeover. There are several new services you should know about. It even seems that a few more Dopples have been captured for combat training. You should go and have a look for yourself.";
D.q[7609] = "I see you have a Bunch of Keys. Give them here a minute.\n...\nThere you go, you can do the dungeon once without needing the key.";
D.q[7610] = "Thank you very much! Thanks to you, the worthy children of the World of Twelve will receive their toys for Kwismas.\nTo reward your generosity, I\'ve prepared several gifts for you. I hope you like them.\nIf you think they\'re too small, my wife will swap them for a larger present. HAPPY KWISMAS!";
D.q[1411] = "Indeeed iit ttaalliees wiiith thee seentiiinels\' eeviiidennnceess.\nThaaaanks ffoor yoouur hellp. Taakee thaat liittlee preeseent too reeward yoouur diiaaboolicaal meeriiit.";
D.q[7038] = "What characteristic should this scroll modify?";
D.q[7043] = "You don\'t have enough Strokens for the exchange.";
D.q[5156] = "Hello, how can I help?";
D.q[5159] = "Ho are you getting on with Elviana Tirips?";
D.q[5232] = "Interesting... I\'ll get people talking about it in my tavern";
D.q[6182] = "We currently have more troops than Brakmar, so we\'ve no great need for new recruits.";
D.q[3206] = "Alright, I\'ll help you get out of here. Keep the key, you\'ll need it if you decide you want to come back again. Oh, and before you leave, I need to give you a new respawn point as the Minotoror\'s curse seems to have caused you to forget a few things. So, let me see...\nThe Korkule sisters\' bedroom? Too dangerous. \nThe Bimd\'Oule Pit? Too deep. \nSarlack\'s gigantic belly? Too humid. \nI tell you what, why don\'t I just make it the same place you had before you came here? Consider yourself lucky, by the way, that I\'m taking you to the exit as well!";
D.q[3204] = "Hello! You want to investigate this labyrinth to see what treasures it holds, am I right? I know what creatures hide inside it, as I\'m one of the best archaeologists on this vast island. Some say that\'s because I\'m the only archaeologist on this vast island, but that\'s not entirely true! The others were so bad, they got lost in the labyrinth. Hahaha. Well, what do you want to know?";
D.q[4521] = "Don\'t say a word. I suppose it\'s Nara who\'s forgotten some of his tools? He\'s lucky someone is going to bring them to him!";
D.q[5157] = "If Amayiro is planning to cause chaos in Brakmar, I\'d be honoured to join in.";
D.q[7612] = "I\'m waiting for other adventurers to get back to see if all of the boxes have been recovered. Come back and see me later, in case there are still a few left.";
D.q[3762] = "Iop left his sword in Incarnam in order to remind us of his glorious power.";
D.q[6490] = "Hahahaha!\nHOHOHOHOHOHOHAHA!!!\nI can smell you from 100 yards, and you dare come ask me for a favour?\nHuhuhuhuhHOHOHO!\nGive me a sapphire and I\'ll tell you where the poison is kept. Unless I change my mind in the meantime. \nHahahaha!\nHOHOHOHOHOHOHAHA!!!";
D.q[5810] = "*Runs hand through hair*\nWhat\'s it about?";
D.q[5652] = "I don\'t know what you\'re talking about. Anyway, that\'s no way to talk to someone older than you. we haven\'t exactly raised our Gobballs in the same field, now have we.";
